<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-81-0445 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper summarizes the trends and developments in the OPEC cartel sincethe Arab oil boycott. It discusses the economic developments among OPECcountries and the impacts on the US economy caused price increases. Itdiscusses the adjustments the US and other world markets are making tocut the amounts of oil consumption. The paper also goes on to discussthe effects of a possible Persian Gulf cut-off of oil to the US and USallies. The effects of falling oil prices on Arab oil producers as comparedto benefits are compared.</TEXT></DOC>